My expertise lies in developing enterprise security products and storage solutions, leveraging my deep technical knowledge in various technologies, including Windows Kernel Programming, Virtualization, and REST APIs.  Throughout my career, I have been dedicated to driving innovation and optimizing product development processes. I have successfully implemented Agile methodologies to enable rapid product development and foster cross-functional collaboration. My passion for team building and mentorship has allowed me to grow and nurture teams of over 50 engineers, creating a culture of continuous improvement and technology adoption. headline: Solutions Architect
summary: Accomplished Technology Leader with 16+ years of experience driving innovation, technology strategy, and scaling solutions in start-up and B2B/Marketplace environments. Proven expertise in leading cross-functional teams, defining business-aligned technology roadmaps, and spearheading high-growth initiatives for renowned brands, including strategic and leadership roles at Reliance Retail Group (JioMart).  Adept at delivering complex, high-performance systems in fast-paced, fail-quick environments. Expert in aligning technology strategies with business goals to foster scalability, operational efficiency, and competitive advantage.
position_description_1: Leadership in Technical Excellence: Orchestrating Scalable Solutions for JioMart.com  Engineered Scalable Backend Systems: Spearheaded the design and implementation of robust backend architectures, empowering JioMart.com to deliver seamless Q-commerce experiences to millions of users, ensuring reliability and scalability  Strategic Nationwide Expansion: Led the strategic expansion of JioMart.comʼs serviceability from Tier 1 cities to PAN India, encompassing 28,000 pin codes. This initiative significantly boosted daily orders to 4 million and attracted 300,000 new users during peak sale periods.  Brand Integration Leadership: Directed the successful end-to-end integration of leading brands such as NetMeds, UrbanLadder, Dunzo, and ONDC into JioMart.com, expanding their online presence and driving revenue growth.  Played a critical role in the conception and execution of jiomartexpress.com - quick commerce model, architecting systems that enabled order fulfilment within a 30-minute window  Comprehensive Catalog Management: Developed and managed a comprehensive catalog and inventory system for over 5 million articles across multiple verticals, ensuring real-time synchronization of catalog, pricing, and inventory across platforms.  Enabling multi-seller (BuyBox) functionality to offer a true marketplace experience to the customers  Unified User Data: Integration for universal user data system across Reliance platforms, streamlining data management and enabling tailored, personalized user experiences.  Seamless API Integration: Successfully coordinated API integrations with third-party services, Finance, IT & logistics partners to ensure flawless operations and superior customer experiences.
position_description_2: Leadership in Technology Consulting:  As a technology consultant, I specialize in guiding large-scale projects, such as IFRS9 model development, from inception to delivery. My role encompasses handling client requirements, overseeing implementation, and ensuring seamless end-to-end delivery. Additionally, I spearhead the smooth onboarding process for new clients across platforms in the Middle East.  Client-Centric Delivery Management:  In Brazil, I assumed leadership of the entire delivery process for a prominent banking client. This involved orchestrating all aspects of the project to ensure client satisfaction and successful outcomes.  Innovative Solutions and Process Improvement:  I played a pivotal role in redesigning and modernizing the existing ETL mechanism, transitioning it to an industry-standard setup. This transformation, leveraging Pentaho Kettle, Kitchen, and Spoon, significantly enhanced efficiency and performance.  Architectural Expertise in Retail Optimization:  I provided architectural design expertise to Inditex, focusing on optimizing packing box selection and warehouse layout management. Through meticulous planning and innovative design, we optimized operations for streamlined efficiency and cost-effectiveness.
position_description_3: Leadership in Solution Development:  Led the development of multiple solutions, ranging from $200k to $1.5M, by providing visionary guidance in technology stack selection, architecture design, and reviews. Managed diverse teams, ranging from 2 to 40 members, ensuring delivery of high-quality solutions within stipulated timelines and with healthy profit margins. This demonstrated our robust technical expertise and paved the way for new revenue streams and projects at ZS.  Innovative Solutions Driving Success:  Pioneered the creation of a Field Assistant bot leveraging personalized analytics, capable of offering comprehensive user support and context-sensitive insights. Utilized advanced data slicing techniques and analytical modules to uncover significant patterns within vast datasets, serving users with concise, tailored information based on individual usage and preferences.  Implemented revenue optimization strategies for airlines through sophisticated capacity planning solutions. Developed a powerful linear and quadratic problem solver using CPLEX and R, enabling airlines to make informed decisions and maximize profitability.  Designed and deployed a contracting decision support solution, enabling data-driven analysis to predict deal profitability. Architected an intuitive front-end analytics engine capable of processing millions of calculations swiftly, delivering sub-second results for enhanced decision-making efficiency.  Impactful Innovation in Service Improvement:  Engineered a sentiment analysis engine for a leading hotel chain, revolutionizing sales trend analysis and service enhancement initiatives. Leveraged advanced NLP engine parsing techniques and data scraping capabilities to provide actionable insights, driving improvements in customer satisfaction and revenue generation.
position_description_4: Enhancing Functionality and Streamlining Processes in Software Solutions  Feature Implementation and Enhancement: Successfully integrated a range of new features into existing solutions using D3 - Differential Deployment Designer. These enhancements significantly improved functionality and user experience, ensuring that the solutions met evolving client needs and market demands. Optimization of CPLEX Modules: Updated and optimized CPLEX modules, leading to improved performance and efficiency across various software solutions. This optimization was critical in enhancing the computational speed and accuracy of complex problem-solving tasks.  CI/CD Process Revamp: Spearheaded the revamping of the CI/CD (Continuous Integration/Continuous Deployment) process for the team, streamlining development and deployment workflows. This initiative resulted in increased efficiency, reduced time-to-market, and a standardized process for managing development and testing environments.  Cross-Functional Collaboration: Worked closely with cross-functional teams to ensure the seamless integration of new features and solutions. This collaboration was essential in effectively meeting project requirements and exceeding client expectations.  Commitment to Best Practices: Consistently adhered to industry best practices and standards in software development, delivering high-quality code within project timelines. This commitment was reflected in the robustness and reliability of the solutions deployed.  Documentation and Knowledge Transfer: Maintained comprehensive, clear documentation throughout the development process, facilitating ease of understanding and knowledge transfer within the team. This approach ensured continuity and supported future development efforts.  Active Participation in Code Reviews: Regularly participated in code reviews, providing constructive feedback and suggestions for improvement. This involvement fostered a culture of continuous learning and growth within the team.
position_description_5: Innovative MDM and Change Management Solution for a Large Pharma Client  Designed and developed a production-ready Master Data Management (MDM) and Change Management solution for a leading pharmaceutical client, introducing a groundbreaking framework code-named TASO. This system was a transformative innovation that empowered representatives across all business units to access a unified, reliable source of truth for their data.  Key capabilities of TASO included:  Centralized Data Access: Enabled users to easily slice and dice data according to their specific needs, ensuring that they could derive actionable insights quickly and efficiently. Streamlined Change Requests: Facilitated the process of requesting changes related to alignment, allocation, and affiliations through a centralized system, improving operational efficiency and data integrity. Flexible State-Management Module: Developed a standalone, highly flexible state-management system, designed as a configurable module that could be seamlessly integrated into any application, enhancing its versatility and adoption across different platforms. Cross-Functional Collaboration: Led the collaboration with cross-functional teams to gather requirements, design the system architecture, and ensure successful integration with existing systems. This cross-team synergy was crucial in aligning the solution with business objectives and technical constraints.  This solution not only addressed the immediate needs of the client but also set a new standard for data management and operational efficiency within the industry.
position_description_6: Startup with a core experience   Virtual Fabric Manager : Implemented FCoE protocol - this helps mitigate the contention at the bridge by reducing the processing required to transform Ethernet packets to Fibre optic packets. This also increases the speed of the network significantly (almost 10 times) Reduce hardware cost Enables cross network connectivity for data centers and super computers. VFM can also manage virtual adapters (vNIC, vHBA) like discovery of Network card in network and send control packet to create virtual adapter, destroy, login to bridge to communicate to different networks.   XViD Transcoding - Decoding/Encoding video and audio from any format to a industry standard. This helps easy exchange, storage and transfer of data. Used the open source Gstreamer framework for implementation. Autoscaled module to guarantee transcoding time irrespective of the file size.
position_description_7: Backup and Recovery Framework Using NDMP:  Comprehensive Backup and Recovery Solution: Designed and implemented a robust Backup and Recovery framework leveraging NDMP (Network Data Management Protocol), specifically tailored for a heterogeneous IT environment. This solution provided seamless data protection across diverse systems and platforms.  Resume from Failure Capability: Engineered the framework with 'Resume ability' from failure, ensuring that backup processes could continue smoothly from the point of interruption, minimizing downtime and data loss.  End-to-End Data Protection: Implemented comprehensive data protection measures, safeguarding data throughout the entire backup and recovery process, from initial backup to final restoration.  Plug-and-Play Capabilities: Developed the framework with plug-and-play capabilities, allowing for easy integration with various systems and storage devices. This feature enabled rapid deployment and simplified the process of scaling the backup solution as needed.  Advanced Encoding and Compression: Integrated multiple levels of encoding and compression within the framework, optimizing storage efficiency and reducing the time required for backup and recovery operations.

position_description_2: 1. SnappyData : https://github.com/TIBCOSoftware/snappydata   TPCH/TPCDS Benchmarking Implemenration :  https://github.com/search?q=repo%3ATIBCOSoftware%2Fsnappydata+kishor&type=code       SnappyData is a tight integration of Apache Spark with Apache Geode (connector mode is also there). Apache Geode:  https://github.com/apache/geode  WAN Replication and Queue Implementation:   https://github.com/apache/geode/search?q=AsyncEventQueue https://github.com/apache/geode/search?q=GatewaySender&type=    Design, coding, testing. GatewaySenders are used to replicate data from one site to another separated by geographical location parallely (ParallelGatwaySender) and serially (SerialGatewaySender)  AsyncEventQueue is a Kafka like mechanism for event stream handling.  Wan auto-discovery :     https://github.com/apache/geode/search?p=2&q=Discovery   Discovery of multiple wan site. Design, coding, tests, data structures choices are driven by me. Java concurrency utilities are used extensively.   Fixed Partitioned Region:   https://github.com/apache/geode/search?q=Fixed    To maintain the data's affinity to a particular node.  Critical aspects of this feature like bucket calculations, bucket rebalancing are designed, coded, unit tested by me.    PR Single Hop:  https://github.com/apache/geode/search?q=*hop  No need for extra hoping with the server cluster to find out the required data  Partition Region Rebalancing: https://github.com/apache/geode/search?q=*rebalance  Whenever node goes gown OR new nodes joins the cluster, Rebalancing op is triggered through a various mechanism which rebalances data buckets (colocated) in cluster for optimized use

headline: HEAD OF INSURANCE | NEW INITIATIVES I EXPONENTIAL REVENUE GROWTH SPECIALIST | STRATEGIC SALES LEADER
summary: With over 18 years of experience in the insurance and banking sector, I am a product and programme expert who delivers growth and enhances ROA across all mediums.   As the Head of Insurance at Centrum Wealth Ltd. I am responsible for the entire P&L for Insurance, new partnerships, product innovation and GTM strategy.  Previously, as the Bancassurance Head at IndusInd Bank, I expanded the business and coordinated customer interaction initiatives. Handling the Affluent Banking channels at IndusInd Bank, I had exceeded ₹496 million in revenue, which represents a 74% increase year over year, as well as net profit growth of 57% and RM activation growth of 68%.  A strategic sales leader who consults high-level executives, boosts business flows, and promotes the desired product mix. I had increased the ROA by 67% and achieved the No. 1 ranking for the SBI Thane Module for two years in a row. I have also successfully transitioned to 100% digital procurement and won the No. 1 Zone Pan India for FY 14, FY 15, and FY 16. My mission is to develop and execute business strategies and plans that are tech-led and focused on attaining greater rates of organic and long-term top- and bottom-line growth. I am passionate about spotting lucrative business opportunities, assessing current and potential market trends, and distinguishing the organisation in an extremely competitive market environment.
position_description_1: In my role as the Head of Insurance at Centrum Wealth Ltd., I spearhead the Insurance P&L, overseeing partnerships, product innovation and regulatory compliance. I evangelise and successfully grow the insurance portfolio, providing tailored solutions for UHNWs and Family Offices  • Initiated and developed strategic partnerships to enhance insurance offerings to the Wealth Management clients part of the Centrum Wealth portfolio • Implemented innovative product solutions and propositions to meet specific wealth management client needs • Achieved significant revenue growth through targeted sales initiatives. • Ensured compliance and successful conduct of insurance audit.
position_description_3: As a Bancassurance head, I delivered growth while enhancing ROA across all mediums and manage white space analysis to expand the bank's business. I exceeded ₹496 million in revenue, which represents a 74% increase year over year, as well as net profit growth of 57% and RM activation growth of 68%. My responsibility includes improving quality measures, including certification, issuance, persistency/renewal, and other KPIs, while increasing RM activation and productivity on the insurance vectors and working together with the Central Executive Committee to plan, agree to, and implement important initiatives.   In addition, I coordinate customer interaction initiatives that are geographically specific and interact with target demographics and industry verticals. I develop and analyse company marketing initiatives while directing the interaction process to guarantee economic growth and enhance quality criteria, including certification, issuance, consistency, and the team and management. Furthermore, to promote goodwill and promote ongoing growth through regular supervision, I report, maintain work, coordinate with cross-functional teams and stakeholders (partners, senior employees, and engagement teams), as well as launch training courses to upgrade the skills of RMs to enable improved solution marketing.
position_description_4: At SBI Life Insurance, I consulted high-level executives at State Bank of India (DGMs, GMs, and CGMs) to boost business flows across locations and successfully expanded the SBI Thane book size in a 4-year period from ₹140 million to ₹720 million  Also achieved the distinction of being the first module in the country to achieve and maintain 100% digital procurement.   By promoting the desired product mix, I strategically increased the ROA by 67%.   In addition, I have also won the No. 1 ranking for the SBI Thane Module for two years in a row, FY 18-19 and FY 19-20, after titling the SBI Bangalore Module as the No. 1 module out of 144 modules of SBI for three consecutive years, FY 15-16, FY 14-15, and FY 13-14. While collaborating extensively with State Bank of India stakeholders.  I oversaw the development and growth of 200+ personnel across many cross-functional teams for the Bancassurance branch and cultivated a strong team culture and a positive work environment by granting financial freedom, encouraging effective discussion, and providing coaching, which led to effective functioning and excellent work-life flow.   Furthermore, apart from this, acted as the main point of contact for customers to handle concerns and escalations with high priority. I have also redesigned slow project management techniques for enhanced organisational and process efficiency while adhering to the most important criteria for quality, cost, and timeline.
